cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the problem of cooperative communication and proposes two protocols for achieving the capacity of the half-duplex Gaussian parallel relay channel. This is a core topic in information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of relays in a network and proposes cooperative strategies for improving the performance of the network. This is a relevant topic in networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes protocols for cooperative communication and analyzes their performance in terms of achievable rates and capacity. This is a relevant topic in systems and control.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the problem of communication in the presence of noise and proposes strategies for improving the quality of communication. This is a relevant topic in multimedia.
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes a general achievable rate based on the combination of the proposed simultaneous and successive relaying schemes. This is a relevant topic in computational engineering.
